{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904586935,"sessionID":"ses_1d1062d55ffe4tPtlf3QgV2gI3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"functions.read:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"The term UBERON:0002346 \\\"neurectoderm\\\" also has a synonym \\\"neuroectoderm.\\\" However, neuroectoderm seems more common amongst the linked cross references, and I also see more results when exact searching Pubmed for neuroectoderm. Are there any reasons why neurectoderm is preferred by UBERON over neuroectoderm?\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd871r0pP\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n10:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please swap label and exact synonym, reference this issue\\n\\nalso please open an issue on the cell-ontology repo to make a corresponding change to any cl terms (you should find them yourself first to save the cl editors the work)\",\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-24T22:44:47Z\",\n12:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n13:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n14:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n15:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n16:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3682#issuecomment-4121905743\",\n17:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n18:     }\n19:   ],\n20:   \"title\": \"UBERON:0002346 \\\"neurectoderm\\\" vs \\\"neuroectoderm\\\"\",\n21:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3682\"\n22: }\n\n(End of file - total 22 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"The term UBERON:0002346 \\\"neurectoderm\\\" also has a synonym \\\"neuroectoderm.\\\" However, neuroectoderm seems more common amo